                "# Oracle Error Codes — Quick Reference\n\nUse this to look up ORA- errors the user reports. Provide the cause and fix.\n\n## Connection & Network\n\n| Code | Message | Cause | Fix |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| ORA-12154 | TNS: could not resolve connect identifier | TNS alias not in tnsnames.ora or LDAP | Check tnsnames.ora, verify service name, check `$TNS_ADMIN` |\n| ORA-12170 | TNS: connect timeout | Network unreachable or firewall | Check host reachability, port 1521 open, security groups |\n| ORA-12541 | TNS: no listener | Listener not running on target | `lsnrctl status` on DB host; check port |\n| ORA-12514 | TNS: listener does not know of service | Service not registered | Check `SERVICE_NAME` vs `SID`; `ALTER SYSTEM REGISTER;` |\n| ORA-03113 | End-of-file on communication channel | Connection dropped | Network issue, DB crash, or killed session |\n| ORA-03114 | Not connected to Oracle | Connection lost after initial connect | Retry; check network stability |\n| ORA-12516 | TNS: listener could not find instance | All dispatchers busy or instance not open | Check PROCESSES/SESSIONS limits |\n| ORA-12518 | TNS: listener could not hand off client | Insufficient processes | Increase `PROCESSES` init parameter |\n| ORA-12537 | TNS: connection closed | Abrupt disconnect | Firewall timeout, idle timeout, MTU issue |\n| ORA-28000 | Account is locked | Failed login attempts exceeded profile limit | `ALTER USER username ACCOUNT UNLOCK;` |\n| ORA-28001 | Password has expired | Password lifetime exceeded | `ALTER USER username IDENTIFIED BY new_pwd;` |\n\n## Constraints & Data Integrity\n\n| Code | Message | Cause | Fix |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| ORA-00001 | Unique constraint violated | Duplicate value in PK or UNIQUE column | Check for existing row; use MERGE for upsert |\n| ORA-01400 | Cannot insert NULL | NOT NULL column received NULL | Provide a value or add a DEFAULT |\n| ORA-01407 | Cannot update to NULL | NOT NULL column in UPDATE set to NULL | Check SET clause values |\n| ORA-02290 | Check constraint violated | Value fails CHECK condition | Verify value against constraint expression |\n| ORA-02291 | Integrity constraint — parent key not found | FK references non-existent parent row | Insert parent first, or verify FK value |\n| ORA-02292 | Integrity constraint — child record found | Trying to DELETE parent with children | Delete children first, or use ON DELETE CASCADE |\n| ORA-12899 | Value too large for column | String exceeds VARCHAR2(n) | Truncate input or increase column size |\n\n## SQL & PL/SQL Errors\n\n| Code | Message | Cause | Fix |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| ORA-00904 | Invalid identifier | Column name misspelled or doesn't exist | Check column names in `USER_TAB_COLUMNS` |\n| ORA-00932 | Inconsistent datatypes | Type mismatch in expression | Explicit CAST or TO_CHAR/TO_NUMBER/TO_DATE |\n| ORA-00936 | Missing expression | Incomplete SQL (e.g., trailing comma in SELECT) | Check SQL syntax |\n| ORA-00942 | Table or view does not exist | Object not in schema or no privilege | Check schema prefix, verify GRANT |\n| ORA-01000 | Maximum open cursors exceeded | Too many open cursors in session | Close cursors/statements; increase `OPEN_CURSORS` |\n| ORA-01403 | No data found | `SELECT INTO` returned 0 rows | Handle `NO_DATA_FOUND` exception or use cursor |\n| ORA-01422 | Exact fetch returns more than 1 row | `SELECT INTO` returned multiple rows | Add WHERE to narrow, or use cursor |\n| ORA-01722 | Invalid number | Implicit TO_NUMBER conversion failed | Use explicit conversion; check data |\n| ORA-01843 | Not a valid month | Date string parsing failed | Use explicit TO_DATE with format mask |\n| ORA-01861 | Literal does not match format string | Date/number format mismatch | Match format mask to literal |\n| ORA-06502 | PL/SQL: numeric or value error | Buffer too small, number overflow, etc. | Check variable sizes and data |\n| ORA-06512 | At line... | PL/SQL error stack trace | Read the full stack; fix at the deepest level |\n\n## Locking & Concurrency\n\n| Code | Message | Cause | Fix |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| ORA-00054 | Resource busy | `FOR UPDATE NOWAIT` found locked row | Retry, use `WAIT n`, or investigate blocking session |\n| ORA-00060 | Deadlock detected | Two sessions waiting on each other | One statement is rolled back; application should retry |\n| ORA-08177 | Can't serialize access | SERIALIZABLE conflict | Retry the transaction; reduce serializable scope |\n| ORA-30006 | Resource busy; NOWAIT specified | DDL found table locked | Wait for active transactions to complete |\n\n## Performance & Resources\n\n| Code | Message | Cause | Fix |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| ORA-04031 | Unable to allocate shared memory | Shared Pool exhausted | Use bind variables; increase `SHARED_POOL_SIZE` |\n| ORA-01555 | Snapshot too old | Undo space insufficient for long query | Increase `UNDO_RETENTION`; optimize query to run faster |\n| ORA-01652 | Unable to extend temp segment | TEMP tablespace full | Add tempfile; optimize large sorts |\n| ORA-01653 | Unable to extend table | Tablespace full | Add datafile or enable AUTOEXTEND |\n\n## PL/SQL Specific\n\n| Code | Message | Cause | Fix |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| ORA-04091 | Table is mutating | Trigger queries its own table | Use compound trigger (11g R2+) |\n| ORA-06550 | PL/SQL compilation error | Syntax error in PL/SQL | `SHOW ERRORS` or query `USER_ERRORS` |\n| ORA-20000 to ORA-20999 | User-defined error | `RAISE_APPLICATION_ERROR` | Check application logic in the procedure |\n\n## Application-Level Errors\n\n| Code | Message | Cause | Fix |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| ORA-00907 | Missing right parenthesis | Syntax error | Check parenthesis matching, quoting |\n| ORA-00911 | Invalid character | Special char in SQL (often `;` in JDBC) | Remove trailing `;` in JDBC execute statements |\n| ORA-00933 | SQL command not properly ended | Syntax error at end | Check for extra clauses, missing keywords |\n| ORA-01002 | Fetch out of sequence | Fetching from closed/invalidated cursor | Re-execute before fetch; check cursor state |\n\n## How to Investigate Unknown Errors\n\n```sql\n-- Get full error details\nSELECT * FROM dba_errors WHERE name = 'OBJECT_NAME' AND type = 'PROCEDURE';\n\n-- Find error text for any ORA code\nSELECT * FROM v$message WHERE error_number = 1722; -- replace number\n\n-- Trace session for debugging\nALTER SESSION SET EVENTS '10046 trace name context forever, level 12';\n-- ... run problem SQL ...\nALTER SESSION SET EVENTS '10046 trace name context off';\n-- Find trace: SELECT value FROM v$diag_info WHERE name = 'Default Trace File';\n```\n",
