                '# Schema Documentation Conventions\n\nWhen the user asks to document a schema, produce documentation following this structure.\n\n---\n\n## Output Structure\n\n### 1. Schema Overview\n\n```markdown\n# Schema: {SCHEMA_NAME}\n**Database**: {DB name or service}  |  **Version**: Oracle {version}  |  **Last Updated**: {date}\n\n## Purpose\n{1-2 sentence description of what this schema supports}\n\n## Statistics\n- **Tables**: {count}\n- **Views**: {count}\n- **Materialized Views**: {count}\n- **Packages**: {count}\n- **Sequences**: {count}\n- **Total Data Size**: {size}\n```\n\n### 2. Entity Relationship Summary\n\nDescribe relationships in text if you cannot draw a diagram:\n\n```markdown\n## Entity Relationships\n\nDEPARTMENTS (1) ──────< (M) EMPLOYEES\nEMPLOYEES   (1) ──────< (M) EMPLOYEES [self-ref: manager_id]\nCUSTOMERS   (1) ──────< (M) ORDERS\nORDERS      (1) ──────< (M) ORDER_ITEMS\nPRODUCTS    (1) ──────< (M) ORDER_ITEMS\n```\n\n### 3. Table Documentation (for each table)\n\n```markdown\n### Table: EMPLOYEES\n\n**Purpose**: Stores employee personal and employment information.\n**Row Count**: ~50,000  |  **Size**: 12 MB  |  **Partitioned**: No\n**Owner**: HR\n\n#### Columns\n\n| # | Column | Type | Null | Default | Description |\n|---|--------|------|------|---------|-------------|\n| 1 | EMPLOYEE_ID | NUMBER(10) | NO | Identity | Primary key |\n| 2 | FIRST_NAME | VARCHAR2(50) | NO | | Employee first name |\n| 3 | LAST_NAME | VARCHAR2(50) | NO | | Employee last name |\n| ... | | | | | |\n\n#### Constraints\n\n| Name | Type | Columns | Reference | Details |\n|------|------|---------|-----------|---------|\n| PK_EMPLOYEES | PRIMARY KEY | EMPLOYEE_ID | | |\n| UK_EMP_EMAIL | UNIQUE | EMAIL | | |\n| FK_EMP_DEPT | FOREIGN KEY | DEPARTMENT_ID | DEPARTMENTS.DEPARTMENT_ID | |\n| CHK_EMP_SALARY | CHECK | SALARY | | salary > 0 |\n\n#### Indexes\n\n| Name | Type | Columns | Unique | Notes |\n|------|------|---------|--------|-------|\n| PK_EMPLOYEES | B-Tree | EMPLOYEE_ID | Yes | Auto from PK |\n| IDX_EMP_DEPT | B-Tree | DEPARTMENT_ID | No | FK index |\n| IDX_EMP_NAME | B-Tree | LAST_NAME, FIRST_NAME | No | Search optimization |\n\n#### Triggers\n\n| Name | Event | Description |\n|------|-------|-------------|\n| TRG_EMP_AUDIT | BEFORE INSERT OR UPDATE | Sets audit columns |\n\n#### Dependencies\n- **Referenced by**: ORDER_ITEMS.EMPLOYEE_ID, EMPLOYEE_TRANSFERS\n- **References**: DEPARTMENTS, EMPLOYEES (self-ref: MANAGER_ID)\n\n#### Notes\n- {Any special business rules, gotchas, or historical context}\n```\n\n### 4. View Documentation\n\n```markdown\n### View: V_ACTIVE_EMPLOYEES\n\n**Purpose**: Active employees with department name for application queries.\n**Type**: Regular View  |  **Updatable**: No\n\n#### Definition\n{Include the SQL or summarize it}\n\n#### Source Tables\nEMPLOYEES, DEPARTMENTS\n```\n\n### 5. Package Documentation\n\n```markdown\n### Package: PKG_EMPLOYEE_MGMT\n\n**Purpose**: Core employee management operations.\n\n#### Public Procedures\n\n| Name | Parameters | Description |\n|------|-----------|-------------|\n| HIRE_EMPLOYEE | IN: first_name, last_name, email, dept_id, salary; OUT: employee_id | Creates new employee |\n| TERMINATE_EMPLOYEE | IN: employee_id, reason | Soft-deletes employee |\n\n#### Public Functions\n\n| Name | Parameters | Returns | Description |\n|------|-----------|---------|-------------|\n| CALCULATE_BONUS | IN: employee_id, fiscal_year | NUMBER | Computes bonus based on tenure |\n\n#### Dependencies\n- References: EMPLOYEES, DEPARTMENTS, AUDIT_LOG\n- Called by: Application layer (Spring Boot / Lambda)\n```\n\n### 6. Sequence Documentation\n\n```markdown\n## Sequences\n\n| Name | Start | Increment | Cache | Used By |\n|------|-------|-----------|-------|---------|\n| SEQ_EMPLOYEES | 1 | 1 | 100 | EMPLOYEES.EMPLOYEE_ID |\n| SEQ_ORDERS | 1000 | 1 | 500 | ORDERS.ORDER_ID |\n```\n',
